reviews.text: Having not been before, I wasn't sure what to expect, but was told Guthrie's was an Alabama experience I had to try. The menu is simple, a plus because it made deciding easier. The employees were pleasant and the food was delicious, fast, and hot.

This restaurant is so well run.  The ladies who were working there when we came in were so joyful, friendly, and were going above and beyond.  It's been a long time since I've experienced that anywhere, much less a fast food place.  The restaurant was extremely clean, and the ladies were cleaning throughout our time there as well.  I was very impressed and those staff people should be given raises for giving that store such a great impression.  I can't say enough about how great it was!

Not only was the food amazing (i love their chicken), but so was the restaurant in general! The second I stepped inside, I noticed how clean it was! I was immediately greeted and about 5 mins after i ordered, i got my food. Normally I don‚Äôt like going to public restrooms, but this one was SO CLEAN!!! There were 2 air fresheners and plenty of paper towels and toilet paper. Overall this was an amazing experience, 10/10 recommend!
Great fried chicken. Flavor you just don't get from the other big chains. Cole slaw, fries, and toast all tops. And the sweet tea is so refreshing on a hot summer day

Ever loved chicken? Is it part of your main diet? You feel like you want to eat chicken for the rest of your life, well here it is. Guthrie's. A matchmade in heaven, although strikingly similar to Raising Cane's, this is Alabama's version.

Service: Nothing too special or too bad, just your regular staff member at the counter, she was nice and all, you know me, I don't like to take pictures of the staff members because they might not like it due to privacy concerns.

Atmosphere: Simple and sweet, something you would see out of a restaurant for sure, bright interior with the lights, checked out the bathroom, clean and not dirty. Someone has definitely been cleaning up around here or maybe not a lot of people have been coming inside.

Food: Again, it's not much to work with, you get 4 things in a box. Fries! Chicken Tenders! Cole Slaw! and to top it off, some toast bread that seems very fluffy to eat. Chicken is rich and crunchy, almost like you're meant to use it with the sauce, it's exactly like Cane's but I'd have to settle a debate and buy both one day and find out for myself. Fries are like a bigger and better version of your typical crinkle fries, just enough seasoning. Cole Slaw might not be for everyone but you can always try it out for funzies.

Oh and they have a drive thru as well ü§£üëç

detailedReviews.author: Anthony Gantt
detailedReviews.text:
I am writing to express my disappointment with the service I received at the Guthrie's location at 4629 US 280, Birmingham, AL. During my recent visit to Birmingham for work, I was excited to see a Guthrie's, as it brought back nostalgic memories from my college days in Tallahassee back in 1999.

However, my experience was far from pleasant. On June 27, 2024, I arrived at the Guthrie's location at approximately 9:42 PM, well before the posted closing time of 10:00 PM. My spouse was in the car waiting for food from Whataburger across the street, so I decided to walk over to Guthrie's to place an order.

To my surprise, the main lobby was already locked. When I explained to the manager that I wanted to place an order, she instructed me to go through the drive-thru. I reiterated that my girlfriend had the vehicle and we would not make it through the drive-thru before closing time. Despite my explanation, the manager continued to insist that I use the drive-thru.

Frustrated, I went to the drive-thru window on foot. I felt disrespected and unheard, especially when the manager assumed I was a delivery driver for GrubHub or Uber Eats despite my repeated explanations. This experience has left a sour taste in my mouth, overshadowing the fond memories I had of Guthrie's from my college days.

I hope you understand the disappointment this has caused and take steps to ensure that other customers do not face similar issues in the future. Based on this experience, I no longer see Guthrie's as the nostalgic and enjoyable place I once knew.

So thinking maybe they are busy on the inside we proceeded to go in to get the ketchup seeing that there are four to five associates currently working that should have been more than happy to help if she was not (wish I had her name). The toasted bread as well - not too brown, but a little 'crunch' to the bite! The slaw was delicious as always.  The entire meal was excellent. Please pass this on to your 'crew.'  Oh, I had eaten at a burger chain a few days earlier and spent just about the same and there was NO COMPARISON!  This place does NOT even have a warmer.  Your food is always going to be FRESH and reasonably priced!
